entries.title: The Hunt
entries.description:
Found her lurking in the marshlands today. Heress - some forgotten thing, neither fully alive nor properly dead. The kind of creature that exists in the spaces between, much like the magic I've come to embrace.
She was stronger than the usual plague-touched beasts wandering these lands. Her eyes held intelligence, cunning, perhaps even a twisted kind of wisdom. For a moment as we circled each other in that flower-dotted marsh, I wondered what she had been before the corruption claimed her.
Then the void whispered, and I stopped wondering.
My shadow word pain wrapped around her like eager serpents, and I felt her life force flowing into me with each drain. No hesitation, no mercy - just the pure, honest exchange of power that the shadows demand. She fought well, I'll grant her that. But I've grown stronger since leaving Silvermoon's pristine halls.
When it was over and her form lay still among the marsh flowers, I felt... satisfaction. Not the hollow victory a paladin might claim, but something deeper. More real. The shadows had tested me against a worthy opponent, and I had not been found wanting.
The hawkstrider watched from a distance, wise enough not to interfere. Even the beasts of this land understand that some battles are meant to be personal.
Another step deeper into the darkness. Another step closer to truth.

entries.title: Power in the Shadows
entries.description:
The magic flows differently now. Stronger. Darker. More honest.
I felt the change mid-battle with those Scarlet zealots near Andorhal - my shadow word pain suddenly bit deeper, my mind blast cracked through their "righteous" defenses like they were paper. The void whispers grew from murmurs to a chorus, and for a moment I understood why so many fear this path.
It's not the darkness they fear. It's the clarity.
Here in these plague-scarred lands, surrounded by the honest brutality of undeath and corruption, I've learned more about true power in a few days than in all my years studying in Silvermoon's pristine halls. There's no pretense here, no gilded lies about nobility and honor. There's only survival, adaptation, and the will to embrace whatever tools you need.
The other adventurers I've met look at me strangely when shadow tentacles erupt from my enemies, when I drain their life to fuel my own. They don't understand that this isn't evil - it's efficiency. The void doesn't judge, doesn't demand righteousness. It simply asks: will you use what works?
Twenty levels, and I finally feel like I'm becoming who I was meant to be. Not the light-touched priest my people expected, but something else entirely.
The shadows celebrate with me tonight.

entries.title: Temporal Convergence with the Bronze Flight
entries.description:
Met Chromie today - a bronze dragon who speaks of time like others discuss the weather. Her offer to traverse the timeways intrigues me. Where others see draconic magic, I recognize something familiar - existence beyond normal progression.
The bronze dragon's temporal energy reminds me of my own transcendence in Spira. She offers glimpses into Azeroth's fractured past when Deathwing's cataclysm reshaped the world. A time of elemental chaos that echoes the spiral of destruction I once knew.
Standing before this diminutive dragon in my shadow form, I feel the weight of new possibilities. The Cataclysm era calls to me - perhaps in that shattered timeline, I'll find fresh understanding of how catastrophe and renewal intertwine.
The timeways open before me. Once again, I step beyond mortal boundaries.

entries.title: Eldinarcus the Rare
entries.description:
The eternal autumn of these cursed lands was painted in brilliant orange hues when I encountered my first rare adversary - Eldinarcus, a creature whose very presence seemed to shimmer with otherworldly power. The contrast was striking: my shadow form wreathed in violet energy against the warm, golden landscape dotted with countless wildflowers.
As I faced this formidable foe, I felt the familiar thrill of a worthy challenge. In Spira, such encounters were trials of the spirit as much as tests of strength. Here in Azeroth, rare creatures carry that same weight of significance - they are not mere beasts, but guardians of hidden knowledge and power.
The shadows responded eagerly to my call as we engaged in battle, and I found myself grateful for the mastery I've gained over this new form. Where once I commanded the finality of death, now I wield the flowing darkness with growing confidence.

The transformation came without warning as I knelt among the wild grasses of these cursed lands. One moment I was flesh and bone, the next I felt myself dissolving into something far more primal - pure shadow energy coursing through my being.
The violet flames that now wreath my form feel both alien and familiar. In Spira, I transcended death through will and sacrifice. Here in Azeroth, I transcend form itself, becoming one with the void that flows beneath all existence. The shadow does not consume me as I once feared - instead, it welcomes me home.
For the first time since crossing worlds, I feel truly myself again. Not the pale imitation of life I wore in Zanarkand's dream, but something eternal and unbounded. The shadows whisper secrets I am only beginning to understand.
This is what I was meant to become - not death's herald, but shadow's chosen vessel.

The shadows whispered to me today as I stood among these ancient ruins with Ranger Jaela. Bones of the long-dead carpet the ground, and the crumbling stones pulse with residual magic from forgotten battles.
As we explored, I felt something shift within me - a familiar darkness transformed by Azeroth's energies. The shadow magic here differs from Spira's death arts, yet feels strangely complementary. Where once I channeled Sin's finality, now I sense the flowing darkness that permeates this realm's spiritual fabric.
Jaela spoke of the Scourge's touch upon these lands, and I recognized echoes of the same cyclical destruction that once plagued my homeland. But here, the darkness offers not absolute ending, but deeper understanding of the balance between existence and oblivion.
Standing in this threshold between light and shadow, I understand that reaching level 10 is more than advancement - it is an awakening. The void calls to me with new clarity.
Level 10 - the shadows have recognized me as their own, and I have accepted their embrace.

Standing on the golden shores of Eversong Woods, I gazed across the tranquil waters toward a distant city that shimmered against the sunset sky. The architecture was unlike anything I'd known in Spiratowering spires and ancient walls that spoke of a civilization's grandeur.
The water rippled gently, reflecting the warm hues of dusk, and I felt both wonder and melancholy. In Spira, I was the High Summoner, guardian of the Fayth. Here, I am but a wanderer learning to commune with shadows that whisper secrets the Old Gods might envy.
I realized this journey isn't about survival, but transcendence. The city on the horizon represents not just a destination, but a symbol of the new understanding I must forge between the faith I once knew and the shadow arts that now call to me.
The Void whispers promises of power, and I am ready to listen. I will master these shadows just as I once mastered the summoning of Aeons.
